Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary.

== Zesty Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @water{1/2%cup}, @coconut milk{1/4%cup}, @butter{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.

> Thoroughly shake coconut milk in container before opening.

> For 4 servings, use ½ cup coconut milk, 1 cup water, 2 TBSP butter, and 1 tsp sugar.

Bring to a boil, then stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and reduce to a simmer.

Cover and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Patties and Green Beans ==

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, ginger, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}.

Form into 10-12 (20-24 for 4 servings) 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

> Swap in beef or turkey for pork.

Place meatballs on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Using a lightly oiled #spatula{}, smash meatballs to make ¾-inch-thick patties.

Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast patties on middle rack and green beans on top rack.

Roast on top rack until patties are cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Thai Chili Coconut Pan Sauce ==

When patties and green beans have 5 minutes left, in a #large pan{}, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz} with remaining @coconut milk{3/4%cup} over medium-high heat.

Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and season with salt and pepper.

Add patties to pan with coconut chili sauce; toss to coat.

Divide rice between bowls; top with patties and green beans.

Spoon any remaining sauce over patties. Sprinkle with @peanuts{1/2%oz}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.